✨ HELLO SEASON 2 OF MISERABLY HAPPY! ✨

The podcast began with a drunk conversation, that eventually took 6 months to actually materialise. Cut to recording in my room, under my blanket to now having a season 2, with such fascinating guests sharing their experiences; I AM GRATEFUL AND OVERJOYED. 🥺🦋

This has been a fruit of love, labour, sweat, hangovers and tears. But it has all been worth it. Ya know it!👀

🧠Talking about mental health, life and experiences has been and will ALWAYS be so important, within our circles, at work, and with ourselves. It is what enriches us, makes us better and allows us to feel, grow and BE. ⚡️

✨Season 2 ✨ has a beautiful guest line up of people I look up to, who inspire those around them and are unafraid to speak their minds. They are all people I’d like to be as I grow. I am ever grateful for being in the same room as them. 

But this season would not have been possible with my teammate, @rohantrails 🥰. Thank you, for everything. You have helped bring these conversations to life and I am grateful. 

Looking forward for this season, and so much more we have in our little kitty that we cannot wait to share! 🤙🏽🤙🏽

The goodness of self love comes in many ways and forms. From grooving to your favourite music to a night in with delicious good. My favourite is a long, warm shower and some extra love with Sadhev’s Coconut Shower Oil. 

Blended with the age old tradition and today’s skincare secrets, the use of Coconut has been ever so important. I personally love the aroma and the extremely rich texture of the oil after it’s been mixed. It’s soft buttery texture just slides onto the skin, leaving it extremely moisturised, soft and supple. 

After all, healthy skin is happy skin! 

Shot and edited by @rohantrails ✨

latestIgtvVideos.caption: life seems to be stuck in a loop. there is no routine, there is no order, there is no normalcy anymore. it’s funny that our whole lives have been lived a certain way, and then something comes along and disrupts our world as we know it. that’s how temporary and fragile things are. so while i cannot actually help this pandemic like the health care workers, policemen, sanitation workers, delivery staff and numerous others, i can change my perspective. i can learn to be grateful for the mundanity of life.

word vomit: the Internet is a bizarre fucking place you guys and it’s been a roller coaster from putting up nail pics to seeing actual war and d*ath within 2 scrolls of each other. the brain is struggling to process between the overstimulation, overselling, over sexualisation and whatnot. are you tired? I’m tired. but it’s so odd - how do i let to and never double tap on a meme when this platform literally changed my life (like many others!). feels like a pendulum between feeling brain dead and just alive enough to feel grateful lol
